<topic template="Default" status="Under Construction" modified="2022-03-17T16:52:07.585+01:00" lasteditedby="Adam" version="2" xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" xsi:noNamespaceSchemaLocation="../helpproject.xsd">
  <title>How do I add a Sketch-Loop?</title>
  <keywords>
    <keyword>How to Video:<keyword>Add a sketch-loop</keyword><keyword>Merge Points</keyword></keyword>
  </keywords>
  <body>
    <header>
      <para styleclass="Heading1">How do I add a Sketch-Loop?</para>
    </header>
    <para styleclass="Heading3_atocs_">Add a sketch-path or sketch-loop</para>
    <para styleclass="Body Text"><text style="font-style:italic;">A </text><text styleclass="Element">Sketch-Loop</text> is a series of sketch-elements that does not have breaks and the <text styleclass="Interface">Points</text> that join the sketch-elements are merged into one <text styleclass="Interface">Point</text>.</para>
    <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo">Add a <text styleclass="Interface">sketch-loop</text> to add to it a <text styleclass="Element">Profile/Extrusion</text> (Solid) or a <text styleclass="Element">Motion-Path FB</text>.</para>
    <para styleclass="Heading4 Toggle_atocs_">About Merge-Points and Coincident-Constraint</para>
    <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo"><table styleclass="Default" rowcount="1" colcount="1">
      <tr style="vertical-align:top">
        <td>
          <para styleclass="Body Text">Each <text styleclass="Element">Line,</text>&#32;<text styleclass="Element">Arc, Blend-Curve </text>has a <text styleclass="Interface">Point</text> at its ends. We call these <text styleclass="Interface">Points</text> the <text styleclass="Interface">start-Point</text> and <text styleclass="Interface">end-Point</text>.</para>
          <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo">To join different sketch-elements, you can:</para>
          <list id="0" type="ul" listtype="bullet" formatstring="&#183;" format-charset="SYMBOL_CHARSET" levelreset="true" legalstyle="false" startfrom="1" styleclass="HowTo Bulleted" style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:8pt; color:#000000;">
            <li styleclass="HowTo Bulleted">make their <text styleclass="Interface">Start-Point/ end-Points</text> coincident - see <text styleclass="T_Menu">Constraints toolbar &gt; </text><link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="MD-Geometry-Coincident" styleclass="T_Menu">Add Coincident</link></li>
          </list>
          <list id="1" type="ul" listtype="bullet" formatstring="&#183;" format-charset="SYMBOL_CHARSET" levelreset="true" legalstyle="false" startfrom="1" styleclass="HowTo Bulleted" style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:8pt; color:#000000;">
            <li styleclass="HowTo Bulleted"><text styleclass="T_Menu">Add Coincident</text> does not remove a <text styleclass="Element">Point</text>. </li>
          </list>
          <para styleclass="HowTo Bulleted">- or -</para>
          <list id="0" type="ul" listtype="bullet" formatstring="&#183;" format-charset="SYMBOL_CHARSET" levelreset="true" legalstyle="false" startfrom="1" styleclass="HowTo Bulleted" style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:8pt; color:#000000;">
            <li styleclass="HowTo Bulleted">merge their <text styleclass="Interface">Start-Point/ end-Point</text> - see <text styleclass="T_Menu">Geometry toolbar &gt; </text><link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="MD-Geometry-MergePoints" styleclass="T_Menu">Merge-Points</link>&#32;</li>
          </list>
          <list id="1" type="ul" listtype="bullet" formatstring="&#183;" format-charset="SYMBOL_CHARSET" levelreset="true" legalstyle="false" startfrom="1" styleclass="HowTo Bulleted" style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:8pt; color:#000000;">
            <li styleclass="HowTo Bulleted"><text styleclass="T_Menu">Add Merge-Points</text> does remove a <text styleclass="Element">Point</text></li>
          </list>
        </td>
      </tr>
    </table></para>
    <para styleclass="Heading4 Toggle_atocs_">Why Merge-Points?</para>
    <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo">You can use a closed <text styleclass="Interface">sketch-path</text> (<text styleclass="Interface">sketch-loop</text>) for a <text styleclass="Element">Profile</text>.</para>
    <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo">You can use an open or closed <text styleclass="Interface">sketch-path</text> for a <text styleclass="Element">Motion-Path FB</text><text styleclass="Body Text">.</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Heading4 Toggle_atocs_"><anchor id="HoverMerge"><keywords><keyword>How to ...<keyword>Merge Points for a Sketch-loop</keyword><keyword>Hover and Merge Points</keyword></keyword><keyword>Video...<keyword>Hover + Drag to merge points</keyword><keyword>Use the Merge-Points tool</keyword></keyword></keywords></anchor><image src="tog_plus.gif" scale="100.00%" figurelistinclude="0"></image><tab /><toggle type="dropdown" print-expanded="true" help-expanded="false" defaultstyle="false" src-collapsed="tog_plus.gif" src-expanded="tog_minus.gif" src-print="none"><caption><![CDATA[Sketch-Loops with the Hover Technique and Merge-Points Tool]]></caption></toggle></para>
    <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo"><table styleclass="Standard" rowcount="1" colcount="1">
      <tr style="vertical-align:top">
        <td>
          <para styleclass="Body Text">There are two ways to merge two Points into one Point: </para>
          <list id="2" type="ul" listtype="bullet" formatstring="&#183;" format-charset="SYMBOL_CHARSET" levelreset="true" legalstyle="false" startfrom="1" styleclass="HowTo Bulleted" style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:8pt; color:#000000;">
            <li styleclass="HowTo Bulleted">Dynamically, as you add the sketch-elements, with the <text styleclass="Interface">Hover Technique</text></li>
            <li styleclass="HowTo Bulleted">Later, with <text styleclass="T_Menu">Geometry toolbar &gt; Merge-Points</text>.</li>
          </list>
          <para styleclass="Body Text" style="margin-top:0px;"><table styleclass="Top Tip" rowcount="1" colcount="1" style="width:auto;">
            <tr style="vertical-align:top">
              <td>
                <para styleclass="Normal"><link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="MD-Geometry-MergePoints" anchor="HoverTechnique">Video of Hover Technique</link></para>
              </td>
            </tr>
          </table></para>
        </td>
      </tr>
    </table></para>
    <para styleclass="Heading4 Toggle_atocs_"><image src="tog_plus.gif" scale="100.00%" figurelistinclude="0"></image><toggle type="dropdown" print-expanded="true" help-expanded="false" defaultstyle="false" src-collapsed="tog_plus.gif" src-expanded="tog_minus.gif" src-print="none"><caption><![CDATA[Why do Sketch-Loops fail]]></caption></toggle>?</para>
    <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo"><table styleclass="Standard" rowcount="1" colcount="1">
      <tr style="vertical-align:top">
        <td>
          <para styleclass="Body Text CAP-ITALICS" style="text-align:left; text-indent:0px; margin-top:0px; margin-right:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; line-height:1.00; background-color:transparent; white-space:normal; page-break-inside:auto; page-break-after:auto; border:none; tabstops:none;"><text styleclass="VariableName">Condition 1: </text><text styleclass="Interface"> Coincident Points, and not Merged</text></para>
          <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo"><text styleclass="Element">Points</text><text styleclass="Body Text"> are not recognized as part of a sketch-loop when they are coincident.</text></para>
          <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo"><text styleclass="Body Text">You must merge the </text><text styleclass="Element">Points</text><text styleclass="Body Text"> into one </text><text styleclass="Element">Point</text><text styleclass="Body Text"> where each </text><text styleclass="Element">Line</text><text styleclass="Body Text"> and </text><text styleclass="Element">Arc</text><text styleclass="Body Text"> join.</text></para>
          <para styleclass="Body Text CAP-ITALICS" style="text-align:left; text-indent:0px; margin-top:0px; margin-right:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; line-height:1.00; background-color:transparent; white-space:normal; page-break-inside:auto; page-break-after:auto; border:none; tabstops:none;"><text styleclass="VariableName">Condition 2: &#160;</text><text styleclass="Interface">Branches</text><text style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt; font-weight:normal; font-style:normal; text-decoration:none; text-transform:none; vertical-align:baseline; color:#000000; background-color:transparent; letter-spacing:normal; letter-scaling:100%;"> &#160;</text></para>
          <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo">You CANNOT merge <text style="text-decoration:underline;">three</text>&#32;<text styleclass="Element">Points</text> into one <text styleclass="Element">Point</text> - for example, the ends of three <text styleclass="Element">Lines</text> or Arcs - you have a <text styleclass="Interface">&apos;Branch-Point&apos;</text>. A <text styleclass="Interface">Branch-Point</text> is <text style="text-decoration:underline;">not</text> O.K.</para>
          <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo">You CAN merge two <text styleclass="Element">Points</text>, then make a different <text styleclass="Element">Point</text> become <text styleclass="Interface">Coincident</text>. This is NOT a <text styleclass="Interface">Branch-Point</text>.</para>
          <para styleclass="Body Text CAP-ITALICS" style="text-align:left; text-indent:0px; margin-top:0px; margin-right:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; line-height:1.00; background-color:transparent; white-space:normal; page-break-inside:auto; page-break-after:auto; border:none; tabstops:none;"><text styleclass="VariableName">Condition 3:</text><text style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt; font-weight:normal; font-style:normal; text-decoration:none; text-transform:none; vertical-align:baseline; color:#000000; background-color:transparent; letter-spacing:normal; letter-scaling:100%;">&#32;</text><text styleclass="Interface">Figures=of-Eight</text></para>
          <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo">A sketch-element can not cross another sketch-element in the same sketch-loop.</para>
          <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo">A sketch-element cannot osculate, or touch, another sketch-element in the same sketch-loop.</para>
        </td>
      </tr>
    </table></para>
    <para styleclass="Heading4 Toggle_atocs_"><image src="tog_plus.gif" scale="100.00%" figurelistinclude="0"></image><toggle type="dropdown" print-expanded="true" help-expanded="false" defaultstyle="false" src-collapsed="tog_plus.gif" src-expanded="tog_minus.gif" src-print="none"><caption><![CDATA[Example sketch-loops]]></caption></toggle>&#32;</para>
